</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="76" pageNumber="784" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="76.[191,1400,714,1299]" pageId="76" pageNumber="784">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[193,545,1073,1102]" pageId="76" pageNumber="784">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Forrest's Rock Squirrel is widely distributed and is presumed to have a large population size but no information is available on current population trends. Lack of knowledge ofits biology may be detrimental to conservation efforts in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
